title: SA complies with the African Continental Free Trade Area requirements
description:
News from Addis Ababa, Ethiopia where the African Union summit is underway ... South Africa has fully complied with the requirements of the African Continental Free Trade Area, after it deposited its instruments of ratification at the African Union.   This now brings to 17 the number of countries that have ratified the agreement. 
For the deal to take effect a minimum of countries must ratify.

For more news, visit: sabcnews.com
